nd Brazil. Among nations, inequality has been decreasing as traditionally poor countries’ economies have caught up with the West. The report shows, however, that inequality has been steadily deepening within almost every nation, though national trajectories vary, suggesting the importance of institutional and policy frameworks in shaping inequality. The World Inequality Report: 2018 will be a key document for anyone concerned about one of the most imperative and contentious subjects in contemporary politics and economics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEconomic historyy21st century. 0aEconomic history-21st century. 0aEqualityxEconomic aspectsvCross-cultural studies. 0aEquality-Economic aspects-Cross-cultural studies. 0aIncome distributionvCross-cultural studies. 0aIncome distribution-Cross-cultural studies. 70(DE-588)4013898-70(DE-627)1063416260(DE-576)208905936aEinkommensverteilung2gnd 70(DE-588)4029560-60(DE-627)1062737870(DE-576)208983120aKapital2gnd 70(DE-588)4047353-30(DE-627)10619481X0(DE-576)209073306aProduktionsfaktor2gnd 70(DE-588)4055746-70(DE-627)1047989200(DE-576)20911522XaSozialer Indikator2gnd 70(DE-588)4113450-30(DE-627)1058293900(DE-576)209476583aEntwicklung2gnd 70(DE-588)4121816-40(DE-627)1057668440(DE-576)209546417aUngleichgewicht2gnd 70(DE-588)4132339-70(DE-627)1056884870(DE-576)209634723aBeurteilung2gnd 70(DE-588)4188065-10(DE-627)1052674220(DE-576)210050284aVerteilungspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4201519-40(DE-627)1051653280(DE-576)210142529aPolarisierung2gnd 70(DE-588)4249243-90(DE-627)1047830280(DE-576)210747730aWirtschaftsindikator2gnd 70(DE-588)4294453-30(DE-627)1041834460(DE-576)210961228aTendenz2gnd 70(DE-588)4304375-60(DE-627)1216401670(DE-576)211067555aAbschätzung2gnd 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic Condition